Hey @mg0:, as sirlotaplot said I added a button to publish all changed galleries (i.e. `content.json`'s) in one go and this goes very quickly. The way I did this is by using the ZeroFrame library and calling `sitePublish` for every single one of them.

The way you could do this is having a little page in your zite (e.g. `sign.html`) that does something along the lines of
```javascript
zn.cmd('siteInfo', [], res => {
  if (res.settings.own) {
    // Somehow get the list of content.json's you wish to sign here
    toSign.forEach(inner_path => {
      zn.cmd('sitePublish', { inner_path })
    }
  }
})
```
It's a bit hacky, but every time you then go to that page it's going to sign and publish all of them.

